                                          BLOCKS IN JAVA
=============================================================================================
=> Block means some part or some piece of information or some piece of code.
=> In java program, we can write 2 types of blocks
                                
                                1.instance block
                                2.static block

===============
instance block
===============

=> If you want to execute some piece of code when object is created then we will go for instance block.
=> Instance block will be executed before constructor execution.
syntax: 
                  
                  {
                  
                  //logic
                  
                  }
==================
Static Block
==================
=> If you want to execute some piece of code when class is loaded into jvm then we go for static block
=> Static block will execute before main() method execution.
syntax:

        static {
        
           //logic
        
           }




