                                                      java.lang.Object.class
                                                ====================================


=> Object is a predefined class available in java.lang package.
=> Object class will act as super class for all the classes in java either directly or in-directly.

Note: If our class does not have any super class then Object class will become direct Super class.
      If our class having any super class then Object class will become in direct super class.
=> Object class having 11 methods, those methods are by default available for every java project.

                          1. protected object clone()
                          2.boolean equals(Object obj)
                          3.protected void finalize()
                          4.Class<?>getClass()
                          5.int hashCode()
                          6.String toString()
                          7.notify()
                          8.notifyAll()
                          9.void wait()
                          10.void wait(long timeout )
                          11.void wait(long timeout, int nanos)

Note: Last 5 methods will be used in Multi-Threading concept.















